				h2 Code the Web
				p Brackets an open source code editor. It's built with JavaScript, HTML and CSS by web developers like you.
				a.other(href="#") Other downloads
				#downloads-list
			section.system-requirements 
				.description 
					h3 System Requirements
					ul
						li Mac OSX 10.6 or newer.
						ul
							li Mountain Lion (OS X 10.8) by default will not allow Brackets to run since it's not being digitally signed yet. To work around this, right click the Brackets app and choose Open, then click Open on the dialog that appears. You only need to do that once -- afterward, launching Brackets the normal way will work also.
						li Windows Vista/7.
						li WinXP w/ Service Pack 2.
						li You should have at least 2 GB of RAM to do Live Development.
			section.update 
				.description
					h3 Frequent Updates
					p We release new features in Brackets about every 2.5 weeks. When a new build is availale you will see a present icon inside the application. For the latest new and release information, follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/brackets">@brackets</a> on Twitter.
